    },
    {
      "question": "What are the objectives for implementing an internal carbon price?",
      "answer": "The objectives for implementing an internal carbon price include conducting cost-benefit analysis, driving energy efficiency, driving low-carbon investment, incentivizing consideration of climate-related issues in decision making, identifying and evaluating financing opportunities, influencing strategy and financial planning, navigating regulations, reducing upstream value chain emissions, setting and achieving climate-related policies and targets, setting a carbon offset budget, stress testing investments, informing credit risk assessments, using an internal price for corporate climate-related engagement/stewardship purposes, and other objectives."
