      "question": "What is the definition of composting (industrial/home) in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Composting (industrial/home) is a process primarily characterized by forced aeration and natural heat production from biological activity that degrades material, which can be done in an industrial facility or at home, and must align with ASTM D6400 for industrial composting and ISO 17088 for compostable plastics."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of end-of-life management in the context of plastic waste?",
      "answer": "End-of-life management refers to the stage of the lifecycle where goods, materials, and substances are no longer in use and go through a management system to process them for preparation for reuse, recycling, or disposal."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of incineration in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Incineration is the process of controlled, high-temperature combustion to destroy, render inert, or reduce waste to ash, excluding Waste to Energy."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of landfill in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Landfill is a permanent (i.e., more than one year) waste disposal site for the deposit of waste onto or into land, which can also be internal, where a producer of waste is carrying out their own waste disposal at the place of production."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of leakage in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Leakage refers to the process of goods, materials, or substances leaving the technosphere (human environment) and accumulating in the natural environment."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of mismanaged waste in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Mismanaged waste refers to goods, materials, or substances that are either littered or inadequately disposed, including disposal in dumps or open, uncontrolled landfills, where it is not fully contained, and waste that is not appropriately transported, collected, or stored."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of preparation for reuse in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Preparation for reuse refers to checking, cleaning, or repairing recovery operations, by which goods, materials, or substances that have reached end-of-life are prepared so that they can be re-used without any other pre-processing."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of production of plastics in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Production of plastics refers to manufacturing processes used to make plastic products, such as polymerization, injection molding, melting, extrusion, and sealing."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of recycling in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Recycling refers to any recovery operation by which waste materials are reprocessed into goods, materials, or substances for the original or other purposes, excluding Waste to Energy."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of waste to energy in the context of end-of-life management?",
      "answer": "Waste to Energy refers to any waste treatment process designed to recover energy from waste in the form of electricity or heat, also called Energy Recovery."
    }
  ]
}
