      "answer": "Biodiversity indicators are communication tools that summarize data on complex environmental issues. They can be used to signal key issues to be addressed through policy or management interventions. Indicators are important for monitoring the status and trends of biological diversity and, in turn, feeding back information on ways to continually improve the effectiveness of biodiversity policies and management programmes."
    },
