      "question": "How do you calculate the carbon footprint of your portfolio?",
      "answer": "The carbon footprint of a portfolio can be calculated using metrics such as weighted average carbon intensity, portfolio carbon footprint, and avoided emissions. The calculation methodology and data sources used to measure the impact of the portfolio on the environment should be explained, including the types and sources of data used, the methodologies and assumptions used to make the calculations, and any further details for the metric used."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the definition of biodiversity footprint?",
      "answer": "The biodiversity footprint refers to the impact of a portfolio on biodiversity, and can be measured using metrics such as Mean Species Abundance (MSA) and Potentially Disappeared Fraction (PDF) of species. These metrics estimate ecosystem condition and measure the average abundance of species in selected groups compared to a natural reference state."
    }
  ]
}
